      "message": "[info] Line 1895: The payload size cap is only enforced at validation time, i.e. after the object has already been fetched (bounded solely by MAX_FETCH_SIZE \u003d 256MB) and written to the local object DB. A malicious/buggy peer can therefore push large COLLAB_UPDATE messages across many device refs and consume disk before they are rejected here. This is defense-in-depth, not blocking, but worth documenting the residual DoS surface (or pruning rejected side-ref objects).",
