      "side": 1,
      "message": "[warning] Line 3649: `docId` is interpolated directly into a git ref name here (`refs/collab/{docId}/{deviceId}`) and into a glob in `logCollabRefs` (`refs/collab/{docId}/*`). If `docId` can ever contain `/`, `*`, or other ref-invalid characters, this breaks in subtle ways: a `/` in docId shifts the namespace depth so that `logCollabRefs`\u0027s `rfind(\u0027/\u0027)` extracts the wrong `refDevice`, and a `*` would widen the glob to unrelated documents. Even if callers currently only pass a hex hash, please validate/reject non-conforming docIds (e.g. assert it matches the expected commit-id charset) before building ref names, so a malformed or peer-influenced docId cannot corrupt the ref namespace or the device-extraction logic.",
      "revId": "6a6105e7c0772864258ce2e3813209907d6bbb66",
      "serverId": "1e26b4c1-6b8c-47ff-9df7-501b633d3b5a"
    },
