      "side": 1,
      "message": "[info] Line 3744: `logCollabRefs` reads/iterates refs without holding `pimpl_-\u003eopMtx_`, whereas `commitToCollabRef` and `fetch` mutate `refs/collab/*` under that lock. This matches the existing lock-free `log()` read path, so it\u0027s acceptable, but a concurrent `commitToCollabRef`/`fetch` can update a ref mid-iteration. Since each device only fast-forwards its own ref this is benign today; flagging so it\u0027s a conscious choice.",
      "revId": "6a6105e7c0772864258ce2e3813209907d6bbb66",
